#: ../../plans.rst:3
msgid "Professional development plans"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:6
msgid "A plan changes what happens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:7
msgid ""
"At different times you may be asked to make a professional development "
"plan, or choose to make one yourself. Many people who have done this "
"previously at work will face the task with reluctance - because the plan "
"has seemed unreal and arbitrary, and because they haven't seen meaningful"
" results from it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:9
msgid ""
"This is really a shame, because a well-made plan is a wonderfully "
"effective tool for success."
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:13
msgid "Dimensions of a plan"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:15
msgid ""
"A good plan contains an aspiration, objectives and commitments. The "
"**aspiration** is what you are reaching for; the **objectives** are what "
"you will achieve along the way; the **commitments** are to the actions "
"you will actually take."
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:17
msgid "They answer three different questions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:19
msgid "What do you *want*?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:20
msgid "What shall you *achieve*?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:21
msgid "What will you *do*?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:23
msgid ""
"They are separate, independent *dimensions* - they often get mixed up and"
" blurred, but they are each a different *kind* of thing. Each one is "
"necessary in a plan."
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:29
msgid "aspiration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:30
msgid "objectives"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:31
msgid "commitments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:32
msgid "where you want to go"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:33
msgid "what you will make happen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:34
msgid "what you commit to doing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../plans.rst:35
